Triple Coconut Shrimp
  --Ben Mims

½ lb peeled and deveined medium shrimp (tails intact)
1 c canned coconut milk
finely grated zest of 1 lime
kosher salt
½ c panko breadcrumbs
½ c unsweetened shredded coconut
freshly ground black pepper
cooking spray
1 small or ½ medium cucumber, halved and seeded
1 c coconut yogurt (or dairy yogurt)
1 serrano chile, seeded and minced

In a bowl, combine the shrimp, coconut milk, lime zest, and ½ teaspoon kosher salt. Let the shrimp stand for 10 min. Meanwhile, in a separate bowl, stir together the breadcrumbs and shredded coconut and season with salt and pepper. A few at a time, add the shrimp to the breadcrumb mixture and toss to coat completely. Transfer the shrimp to a wire rack set over a baking sheet. Spray the shrimp all over with cooking spray. ransfer the shrimp to the air fryer and cook at 400F until golden brown and cooked through, ~4 min. Move the shrimp to a serving platter and season with more salt. Grate the cucumber into a small bowl. Stir in the coconut yogurt and chile and season with salt and pepper. Serve alongside the shrimp while they're warm. Yields 2-4 servings.
